article.description: Micah Seaborn scored 14, while Austin Tilghman and Chris Brady added 12 points apiece to help top-seeded Monmouth beat No. 8 seed Rider 59-48 in the quarterfinals of the Metro Atlantic Athletic C
article.headline: Monmouth beats Rider 59-48 in MAAC tourney quarterfinals
article.linkText: Monmouth beats Rider 59-48 in MAAC tourney quarterfinals
article.story: ALBANY, N.Y. -- Micah Seaborn scored 14, while Austin Tilghman and Chris Brady added 12 points apiece to help top-seeded Monmouth beat No. 8 seed Rider 59-48 in the quarterfinals of the Metro Atlantic Athletic Conference tournament Friday night. Monmouth will play either fourth-seeded St. Peter's or No. 5 seed Fairfield in the semifinals Sunday. The Hawks (26-6) shot just 32 percent from the field -- their fourth-lowest percentage this season -- but hit 18 of 21 foul shots and converted 21 Rider turnovers into 24 points while limiting the Broncs (13-20) to 16-of-46 shooting (35 percent). Rider took a 6-2 lead nearly four minutes in, but went scoreless for the next six-plus minutes until Kealen Ives hit a 3 to pull within five with 9:40 left in the half. The Broncs didn't make another field goal until Ives' layup with one second left in the half. Xavier Lundy led Rider with 14 points.
